HEADWORD: Telephotograph
<hw>Tel`e*pho"to*graph</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>th^le</grk> far + <ets>photograph</ets>.]</ety> <def>a photograph
transmitted and reproduced by telephotography.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>a photograph made with a telephoto lens.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> telephoto.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

